com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.activities

Class ActivitiesRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<T>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.PaginatedRequestExecutor<Activities>
        • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.activities.ActivitiesRequestExecutor

  • public class ActivitiesRequestExecutor
extends PaginatedRequestExecutor<Activities>
    Request executor provided by ActivitiesApi. Use this class if you want to fetch activities through fluent API in chained fashion, for example: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   Activities activities = kontaktCloud.activities().fetch()
      .startIndex(5)
      .maxResult(10)
      .execute();
